Nick Clegg is to embark on three days of door knocking in his Sheffield constituency after a shock poll showed he is on course to lose his seat at the general election .
The Deputy Prime Minister is trailing Labour by 2 per cent in his formally rock-solid Lib Dem constituency , Sheffield Hallam .
Mr Clegg won his seat in 2010 by a huge margin .
Today he says the Lib Dems were confident of Friday , Saturday and Sunday .